    <string name="tv_game_rules">
    <![CDATA[
    <b>Base rules</b>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                 1. Each player has 6 pits with 6 stones each and a final well to his right.
            </li>
            <li>
                2. The moves are alternating and counterclockwise.
            </li>
            <li>
                3. For a turn all the stones are taken from a game pit and stone by stone, including
                the own end pit, with the only exception of the opponent, distributed in a counterclockwise
                direction.
            </li>
            <li>
                4. It is played until all the stones have disappeared from the game pits. The player won,
                which has the most stones in its final pit.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    <p>
        <b>Extended Rules</b>
    </p>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                1. If you finish by distributing the stones in its end pit, you may draw repeatedly.
            </li>
            <li>
                2. If you succeed in getting into a previously empty pit with the last stone, you
                get this one stone, plus all opposing stones credited to its final pit.
            </li>
            <li>
                3. If a player no longer has a stone in his pit after his turn, the opponent gets
                all the remaining pieces on the board into his final pit.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    ]]>
    </string>
